<Base title="About — Ming Ma" description="Ming Ma's background: 15 years building products at Facebook, ByteDance, Scroll, Tranchess and more.">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    I started as an engineer, became a data scientist, then stumbled into product management and never looked back.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Facebook</strong> taught me how to think at scale. <strong>ByteDance</strong> taught me how to move fast.
    <strong>Web3</strong> taught me that chaos can be a feature.
  </p>

  <p>
    At <a href="https://tranchess.com" target="_blank">Tranchess</a> I helped steward a DeFi protocol through a $1.8B TVL peak and a full bear market — and came out the other side.
    At <a href="https://scroll.io" target="_blank">Scroll</a> I parachuted in to run the mainnet launch, then built the product team from scratch.
    We shipped <a href="https://scroll.io/canvas" target="_blank">Canvas</a> and Origin NFT — nearly a million NFTs minted.
  </p>

  <p>
    These days I'm most interested in what happens when AI becomes a real work primitive — not just a writing assistant,
    but the thing that runs your team, your store, your thinking.
    I'm running experiments: building an e-commerce brand (<a href="https://whispertothepearl.com" target="_blank">Whisper to the Pearl</a>) with AI agents,
    exploring AI-native team management, and looking for the startup idea that only makes sense now.
  </p>

  <p>
    I'm open to interesting problems. If you're building something that fits — or just want to think out loud —
    <a href="mailto:mamingming@gmail.com">reach out</a>.
  </p>

